title: Trump Gets Fired
description:
He seemed cool, calm and collected in the other room, waiting for his coffee (which he was assured was for closers). However, as the dulcet tones of Blake’s hypercapitalist putdowns filled his ears, he felt a warmth in his pants that could only be described as the high-pressure evacuation of bowels that had spent a lifetime damming the riverbed of feces with over-processed meat discs. Indeed, the first shit he had taken in decades finally let loose, and it wasn’t a small handful of struggle nuggets like in the past. No, readers, this was a piping hot surge of the wet brown, an astonishing geyser of human jet fuel that propelled the man through the roof and into the sky, wind whipping at his cheeks, carrying him ever further into the cold recesses of space. As the atmospheric frost stopped his tears dead in their tracks and coagulated over his trembling salmon lips, a final word escaped between them, the last anyone would ever hear: “Patriarchy.”

If you’re charmed by this fairy tale ending but know that it isn’t remotely true, then you also know there’s tons of work to be done. Finish whatever you’re drinking, enjoy the rest of the day, wake up and then go here to find a list of Georgia organizations that will help get out the vote for the upcoming runoff elections.

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Ho5HxLJhuWxy1QKzi4_7Ryt6Nvk2wm3RakOgeGiOWK0/edit#gid=0

title: Trump Golfs
description: This hole is a 9-par, which sounds easy until you see all the cross traps. Good luck putting your way out of this one - though if your mental game is strong, you won’t even think about the massive bodycount for one solitary second.

title: The Agony of Covid de Mayo
description: When our great grandspawn tell the tales of this day, huddled around the tire fire in the flickering light of the long dead moon, they will whisper it like a prayer - a hymn to the forgotten Cinco, the "lost rager," the day of the orphan brewskis. They'll shudder at the thought of the unchugged pitchers of frozen strawberry margs at Señor Frog’s, the uneaten complimentary queso dip. Then, in honor of the brave men and women who stayed the fuck inside like responsible people, they will ceremoniously bash their heads with an open fist until it's time to find and eat a mutated jackal.

title: Rationing
description: The W.H.O. has been very clear about this: Drink all the wine, and buy as much as you can at the store. Wait that can’t be right. Oh, that’s the Wine Hoarders Organization. Well, the C.D.C. says to get plastered and scream “GRAPES” from your rooftop at all hours—goddammit, sorry, that’s from the Center for Downing Cabernet. Here’s one from A.A.: E.A.T.S.H.I.T. Oh I see, A.A. stands for Angry Acronyms. Well, this solved nothing. I’m gonna headbutt my stove for five hours

title: Harold vs Mothra
description: Frankly, Harold shouldn't have been talking mad shit.

title: 5SF Pilot - "Apocalypse How
description:
A few years back we teamed up with amazing producer Jonathan Cane to make an educational/comedy show based on real science about how man's actions could lead to the end of the world! Sounds fun right? Well the networks didn't think so.

Well, in these bleak times we thought it would be a good idea to share a giggle about the end of the world. So here it is, our pilot taster about genetically engineered tomatoes that will kill us all!

Enjoy!

title: Clinical Trials
description: When you hear the news talk about how our medical workers are heroes, this is who they're referring to. The only person. No one else is a hero, not even Goku. Fuck him. There should only be one statue ever made, of this one lady, in one town square, and that's it. Melt down the statue of your false idol Goku, the one sitting on the National Mall, and use the gold to make one of her.

title: 5SF BTS: I Love You, My Husky Outtakes
description:
This week of 5SFs began as a means of plugging Brian's animation kickstarter. It ended in cream, puppets, bones and tears.

Thank you to everyone stationed at the "new" 5SF house (we're not calling it that, I promise), the tireless Marisa Gérardin on camera / dead body duty, Maria on cream-slop duty, everyone who watched the live cream-stream, and everyone who backed or spread the word on "Under the Haunted Moon." Love you all.

title: Murder Detectives
description:
[Brian's Kickstarter has finished! But you can still enjoy this 5SF if you like. Actually, you can't, leave now.]

Operation Husky Sons was an unmitigated success. Using the energy of the Interdimensional Flux - caused by cloning unthinkable scores of crime-identifying children - we were able to ensnare the chief in his own bones. All right, team, let's roll out to the Taco Bar and round up a few meaty tortillas. Margs on me.

Actually team, you can all pile in the Flux Wagon. The new recruit and I are going to ride in my car. If you get there first, you know my usual order.

.

Are they gone? Hmmm. Yes, I see them piling in. Okay rookie, I'm going to tell it to you straight. I wasn't happy with your performance today. I know, it's your job as a newcomer to be seen and not heard, but frankly I didn't see you strut your stuff out there either. Could've used more hustle when it came to cloning the husky sons. And your resume says you have experience in bone entrapment, but Vasquez said you were asking lots of questions about the Fluxer. Lots. Of questions.

On my team, I need leaders and players. "Layers," I call 'em. They lay the pipe to link up the flow, for end-to-end delivery of chief-trapping product. They fux with the flux, they're locked into the bone zone. And I don't see you laying pipe with my team. Nope, you're not getting tacos with us. In fact you're not allowed to get tacos ever again. Now get out of here before I stuff you into the head closet.

title: The Famous Body Finders
description:
[Brian's Kickstarter has finished! But you can still enjoy this 5SF if you like. Actually, you can't, leave now.]

Tales of the terrible two swept the whole damn continent, far and wide. The Finder Killers, they called them. Killin' innocent hikers, then settin' off for a hike themselves, happenin' upon the body they just disposed of, seekin' fame and fortune. I never believed it much myself, them wild yarns. But then again, I'm just an innocent ol' country describer, sittin' up here on my prized rocker that I cut down myself from the wartime oak that sat out in my Pappy's thistleyard. Nobody pays me much mind these days, me and my descriptions. Yep, my children, my grandchildren, all killed and later found by the Finder Killers. Damn shame. Thanksgiving ain't quite the same without my alive family to hand off the thanks to. Welp, that low winter sun is dippin' its brow across the far rocky range, and the grasshoppers are trillin' their tune of copulation. Reckon I'll affix my fingers to this here fiddle and play this porch a little tune.

title: Happy Time Cream
description:
[We shot this 5SF live on Monday's stream, all to support Brian's now-finished Kickstarter campaign! Thanks for tuning in if you watched.]

Warning: Do not eat Happy Time Cream. All recipes requiring the use of Happy Time Cream have been created by terrorists. These terrorists are unhappy people who do not have access to Happy Time Cream. They are unhappy because they have lost everyone they know to Happy Time Cream. If they did gain access to Happy Time Cream, they would die because they would eat the cream, which you absolutely must not do. We can't fully explain why these terrorists are behaving the way they do, but regardless, their recipes are war crimes and they need to be stopped - perhaps the best way to stop them would be by giving them the Happy Time Cream they so crave, but it's a really brutal way to go and we can't live with ourselves if we did that. Also, do not apply Happy Time Cream to the face.

title: 5secondfilms Ultimate Halloween Compilation Year1-9
description:
Well.... it looks like I forgot to add a whole Halloween years worth of 5secondfilms. My bad. 2000 films + 10 years of making them some slipped through the cracks. My bad. To make it up to you I sprinkled a bunch of "horror/macabre" 5sf as well. Love you all. (Sorry. Rousselet)

Happy Halloween!

title: Huggins
description: In the genre of "Desperately needy toys," Huggins was always the bridesmaid, never the bride - handily outsold by such contemporaries as Druggins, Fuggins, Chuggins and Buggins. Buggins in particular was a smash hit, since kids always be buggin'.

title: The Nice List
description: It's difficult to make the Nice List, actually. If you're on the Naughty List, it just means you get lame gifts. And when you think about it, haven't all your childhood gifts turned out to be meaningless chunks of plastic that you got too obsessed about? Yeah, chief. That's cuz you never made the Nice List. But Pete Bouchard? Annie Cresswell? Robin Hagle? Kelly Van der Pelt? Brad Botanel? Kieran Conway? Davey Greenwald? James Patrick? Ronald Finger? Devon Palmer? Orbert Handler? Igor Chalworth? Hazel Hansenr? Trevor Holdham? Ruby Hansen? Edgar Hewell? Gabriele Falasca? Morgan Schaefer? Grayson Metzbower? Giuliano Guttlein? Alexander Ferrer? Kurt Skeatborde? Samantha Winch? Dave Oaktowers? Your best friend, Jack Tacklebox? Crandon Bews? Quiff Anderson? Lil' Big Cooper? Yuriy Silaev? Ghoulius Mayweather? Ellie Shatterstar? David of Smeg? Yentl DeGentlemen? Pubert Jones? Franklin Nilknarf? The Tactical Orphans? Sizzler? Hootie? Street Deacon? Erect Bee? Unironischer Antinatalist? Strong Chinchilla? Jazz Hater? Crazz Bazzler? Titan Fritochip? The knowledge that when the last person who remembers us dies, we are truly gone from this Earth? Viceroy Chandler Bing? Yeah, they made the Nice List. And they got the best gift of all: Rapid improvements on their nuclear capabilities in the past few years.

title: Family Tree
description: Somehow, Needles McBristletrunk always harbored a sneaking suspicion that he was not of this land, on account of how his dad could not seed the ground with the passing of a stiff breeze, or bear fruit from the joints in his limbs. And yet, his father's calm voice reassured him all the same. "I am a tree, too. I too am a tree. I am a true tree, son, truly I am your tree dad. Everyone you meet is a tree. All things are trees. That asshole dog is a goddamn tree." Needles thought about this mantra now - about the peace it used to bring him when his sapling head would fill with worries at night - and came to the realization that he was always, in a way, alone in this savage world of paperwork, talk radio and fingernails. He proceeded to weep in the way trees do, when it is time to grieve: By secreting the delicious sap that the sapsucker birds so love to eat. His tears fueled their powerful bodies for days to come until he could cry no more, and, full of holes and regret, he rotted away in that bedroom, dressed in his Christmas finest when the police finally found both of them.

title: Behoof
description: Her shoe addiction tore their marriage apart. Also he tore her apart for meat. It's a terribly sad story, I know, but not an unusual one. These days, 50% of all marriages end in meat.

title: A Broken Toy in Santa's Workshop
description: Santa's gonna be mad! Well, "mad" in the sense that this world in which the concept of Santa exists, perpetuating the idea of his presence as some sort of tangible entity, is psychotically mad - therefore, the only way to mesh with a world that endorses such fiction is to blast hardcore rails of cocaine and drink until completely numb.

title: Ugly Sweater Contest
description: For Thomas Fugly, every day was an ugly Christmas sweater contest, not just because of everything going on with his face, but because of his dogged determination to promote his branded merch. Alas, Fug by Tom Fugly never really took off as a line of casual hideouswear and he had to go back to his day job of being a foot model for Tinactin.

title: Clint Hates Hats
description: The hats would get their revenge, however, when their deaths summoned the ancient Head Accessory Gods from the oceans to cover the Earth and crush everyone underneath, in the action-packed sequel, Pacific Brim.

title: Cyclops Has No Friends
description: One of Cyclops' lesser-known powers in the comics is his inadvertent ability to push off the ruby quartz glasses that hold back his optic blasts, if he "thinks about the logic of the glasses too much." Professor Xavier was always able to keep Scott from thinking about this by placing images of cool cars, surfboards and hamburgers in his mind - effectively distracting him for years. That is, until he met The Questionnaire in X-Factor #70, and sat down for a tragic game of cards.

title: Butter for the Best Boy
description: Police would later describe the scene of the crime as "undoubtedly a suicide" and "unquestionably Alec must have the warm buttered roll, for he is the finest boy I ever did see. The other boys daren't sneak a morsel of his golden moist breadstuff, for their finery is lacking and their demeanour less deserving." The judge threw all of this out in court years later, when it was determined that the officers were bribed with free licks of the piping hot butterbread, but still decreed that Alec was the best boy. Because look at him. Look at the boy.

title: Black Mirror S04E07
description: Plot Synopsis: When Rousselet downloads the new Giphy package meant to improve his life, it makes everything worse. Anyone born before the year 1988 will probably find it sneakily profound, anyone who's too young to even really remember 9/11 will think it's the lamest paranoid-Dad shit ever.

title: Driver's Test
description: When I failed my driver's test the first time, I was pretty upset. People younger than me were driving already, and I was denied access to that all-important Next Step Into Adulthood. I went for an angry jog to take my mind off of it, and then a skull with wings chased me into a ditch and impregnated me with the knowledge of my future wife's death.

title: The Great David Lee Roth Diarrhea Blowout
description: David Lee Roth's incontinence problem became so unavoidable on their 1984 tour that the band was forced to change several of the song titles, just so the crowd would understand why Diamond Dave was pissing and shitting into his tights while continuing to sing. "Jump" became "Dump," "Hot For Teacher" turned into "Hot Urethra," and after changing into his clean night-time trousers to finish out each show, Dave would sing a version of "Panama" called "Pajamas." Concert-goers were impressed by the band's commitment to the performance art, and noted that the pajamas Dave was so proud of were indeed quite fresh. DLR soon left the band to form his own supergroup where "all the songs would sound like shit on purpose," and Van Halen carried on with Sammy Hagar, known as the Red Rocker because of how much blood often turned up in his stool.

title: Smell Mop Who?
description: Sadly, Joey would never come to know his long-lost brother, Smell "Smell Mop" Mop Scoma. Police would later find a man curled up in the employee bathroom at a nearby Rite-Aid, dead from smelling far too many unseemingly mops and mop materials. In his pocket, a letter that read, "No one will miss me. I don't even exist. Signed, Smell Mop." The cops simply refused to believe this was the guy's real name, so they dumped his body in the reservoir and got Shakey's pizza for a job well done.

title: 5SF BTS - We Found This On the Body
description: We found these outtakes on the body, it's just...Paul riffing and everyone else cracking up?

title: Identifying Marisa's Body
description:
That was all it took to seal the deal. No facial recognition, no dental work, no fingerprints. Even the victim's family said "If there ain't haffameatbal nearby, then it ain't my beloved daughter." Perplexed, bewildered and oddly hungry, the detective had no choice but to write "Metbal (0.5)" in his report, and close the case forever.

The Havvameeboll Killer would continue to roam free in the hillsides of Silverlake for decades to come.

title: The Highlight of Paul's Career
description: Paul didn't have the heart to tell Luis Guzmán that Vine technically died, but was coming back, but in that time had made millionaires out of psychopaths, even though Vine never made any money, which is what killed it, which is what also killed 5SF, which was also kind of back in a strange way. Some things you just don't tell to Luis.

title: The Alcoholic
description: His last words were "Happy Birthday Dear Risa / Happy Birthday To Y--" Once the wreckage was cleared away and the bones identified, his grieving parents spared no expense, burying him with an Eternal Flame flickering on top of his grave. Risa showed up to pay her respects and the entire graveyard burned down, killing at least 50 other mourners nearby. When the whole town turned out for a candlelit vigil to honor the dead, she was explicitly not invited to attend. However, after a quick purchase from the mustache store, she slipped right through and the entire town died.

title: The Longest Snowball Fight in Recorded History
description:
The Kormanda Nebula, deep in the Outer Rim.

Mar'del, the emissary for the Space Neolutionaries of Outer Warfare, marched down the defrag hallway surrounded by her guards. All Protaks, all fully armored with the highest Rim gear. They would need to be. She was meeting with none other than the battle captain of the One Day Tribe himself, and could leave nothing to chance, no matter what neutral ground he claimed to receive her on.

Renzi Bain, captain of the Blizzard Armada Liberation League, sat calmly in a cold chrome chair in the middle of the massive room. No weapons, no guards. Even his hands were made visible, on his lap. As Mar'del entered the room, she took note of his seeming harmlessness. She sensed a trap, but knew that in order to advance, she would have to respond with a show of good faith - and nodded for her guards to lower their weapons and remain at ease.

"[I see you spared no expense with your backup dancers there,]" Growled Renzi in his crude tribal tongue. "[I'm beginning to get the impression you don't trust me.]"

"[And why would that be, I wonder,]" Volleyed Mar'del, displaying a surprising grasp of Renzi's language. "[The last time we met, you were bathed in the frost of our cannons on New Saturn. Did you think I wouldn't anticipate a return engagement?]"

Renzi said nothing. Beads of sweat formed on his forehead. Sensing doubt in his own strategy, Mar'del smiled and softened in an attempt to lure him closer to the diplomatic table.

"Let us speak in the tongue of our ancestors," She said. "It's what they would have wanted, after all this bloodshed."

"How do you know what they would have wanted?" Renzi grunted, more sweat coalescing on his brow. He almost appeared ill.

Mar'del expected this meeting to be more difficult. She looked off into the inky vastness of space outside the massive windows, agreeing. "It's true, I suppose. So much time has passed. Who can say what was fact or fiction any longer?" As she pondered that thought, Renzi wiped the sweat off his face, practically pooling in the palms of his hands.

"How can you be sweating, Renzi? This room is so cold."

"I'm sweating because I took a pill to induce it earlier," he muttered under his breath. Then he looked up at her. "And it IS cold in here, isn't it? Cold enough...to crystallize."

His hands unveiled his masterstroke: A snowball carved entirely from the sweat of his skin. He plunged it deep into her face, spraying her with wet frost, and he atomized out of the room before her guards could respond. The only trace of his presence was the cold liquid on Mar'del's fuming face, and his low chuckle echoing in the distance.

She stood up, wiping herself clean. The war would continue. It would always continue.

title: And Now
description:
Unable to read the writing on the wall, Samantha's boyfriend instead rushed to his Facebook feed to get more info on his crumbling love life. Granted, half of the stuff on Facebook was incomprehensible gibberish to him, but the other half was cool videos about cats who can dunk or pictures of friends' babies he pretended were cute. After an hour of feverish scrolling, he finally found another video with Samantha and this dude with the glasses. They were holding hands on a beach.

"Weird thing for a friend to do with Samantha, my obvious girlfriend," he said aloud to himself, but soon the video began revealing more. They stopped walking. Samantha held Glasses Dude's other hand now too, and they looked deep into each others' eyes. Their lips drew closer and closer.

He watched every inch of their body language with rapt attention. Nothing could rip him away from the screen.

Just then, the video paused at the halfway point to run an ad about Trivago or something dumb. It would be an entire 30 seconds before the video resumed, and Samantha's boyfriend clicked away, disgusted with the state of modern advertising.

title: Do You Know Who My Father Is
description: His eventual appearance on Maury, in an episode titled "Who Shall Claim This Boy," resulted in at least 100 daddies stepping forth to announce their claim over the blue polo child. A tournament of blood and champions was promptly set forth, with each would-be daddy dazzling the crowd with their incredible moves and tricks. One by one, as the skulls were caved in and the colosseum grew evermore stained with blood, the final two daddies faced off against a surprised opponent: Maury himself, who grew fond of the boy and, with steam emerging from his nostrils as he chuckled haughtily, chose to enter the tournament to lay claim. Neither daddy was a match for Maury's incredibly OP specials, and soon the child was slung over Maury's powerful shoulder, carried off into the darkening horizon of the blood-red sun.

title: Missed Call
description:
Kelly and Dumpster Jo hit it off right away. Their relationship blossomed out of the ashes of an old flame. Friends, family, and mall police all commented on how perfect they were for each other. Soon they were engaged, and their wedding was truly a sight to behold - the dress made out of layers of flowing cardboard, the cake made out of tossed-out cake from the cake shop, the mall police crashing the wedding to break everything up. Sure, a few things went wrong here and there on the big day, but it didn't matter: Nothing made Kelly happier than finally locking down the woman of his dreams, Dumpster Jo.

Oh, you thought Dumpster Jo was the homeless guy, huh? That just shows what an intolerant person you are. So quick to judge, so keen to file people away. You could never have a love like Kelly and  Joann, who got her nickname from all the times she'd take a shit in a dumpster for fun.

Your intolerance makes me sick. You don't deserve this heartwarming tale. I'm going to end it right here. May you find peace with whatever hate you carry around inside your heart.

title: Timmy's Dying Wish
description: Timmy's quick thinking, however, was not enough to save him from the medical bills to follow - a payment to be made in "either blood or victory," which required venturing to the Mountains of Oor to pluck the Horn of Miracles from atop the crown of the Liquid Night Beast. Luckily, Timmy was able to convince another dying kid to wish that the Liquid Night Beast stopped caring about his earthly possessions, so all was well.

title: Broken Clocks
description: Major credit cards? No! Also, we are dog and child friendly! Do not bring them in. We are closed but the lights are so bright and it's driving me crazy that the light switch isn't working. Please eat shit. Do not come here while we figure this thing out. We love you but we'll be forced to kill you. I don't have a lunch break. I ate a clock yesterday and now my body is ticking. Why do they work inside my body? I'm dyin' here guys, please let me kill you. Come find me and get ready to die, we're closed.

title: Big in Japan
description: BoywhowillonedayplaythepianowithwhatIhopetobeamighty Johnson had a lot to live up to, growing up as he did under the shadow of two master pianists: His father, Youngboywhoshallharnessthepowerofhisingeniousballsacktocommandeerthesaxophone Johnson, and his father before him, Reggie Johnson - who could fuck a bassoon real good.

title: 5sf's Comments of the Week PLUS Kickstarter Update #1 - 5/27 - 5/31
description:
We have several announcements about our Kickstarter! But first, click here if you haven't visited the page already: http://goo.gl/ozvtv

Skip to 3:26 to get right to the comments, but if you do that, why not take some of the time you saved by reading about our Kickstarter announcements right here?

...

People looking to get involved with all the slicing and dicing include Patton Oswalt, Andrew WK, Peter Stormare, the guys from BriTANicK, Freddie Wong, TomSka, Beck Bennett, and more to come too! This film is going to be a huge homecoming party for us and all of the awesome people we've met along our five-year career!

On June 20th, we'll be hosting a four-hour STREAM-A-THON...LIVE! At the YouTube Space in Playa Vista. There'll be great music, rapping from Paul, stand-up comedy, sketches, and boatloads of interactivity, starring us and several surprise guests! Watch from home, or be one of the first 20 people to pledge $60 on our Kickstarter page to receive an exclusive invitation to the event!

Pledge $200 (or add onto your pledge to arrive at the $200 level) and you can have your very own 5sf idea become a reality! Pitch us your concept, we'll workshop it with you, produce it and put it on our sites with your name credited!

One lucky backer has already pledged at the $666 level to receive an exclusive video message from Satan (Ben Gigli)! We promise that if FIVE more people (six total) pledge at this level, we will listen to the fans and finally deliver unto thee...a DEVIL WEEK at 5sf!

And if all that isn't enough, we're heading back to Reddit for another AMA, this Tuesday June 4th! We're a big, big group - and our goal is to answer as many questions as humanly possible! Seriously, ask us anything. We're not shy, as you've figured out by now.

Finally, we address some questions about pledging for those without credit cards or those living outside America. Please visit the FAQ on our kickstarter page (http://goo.gl/ozvtv) to see if our answers help!

We are so thrilled and honored by the kind words and donations you guys have sent our way, it really means everything to us. If you don't have a dollar to spare, believe me, we understand...every little thing helps, including spreading awareness about the project to your friends, your Twitter or your Facebook!

Follow us at http://twitter.com/5sf to stay up-to-date on everything! Thanks again!!

title: Door-to-Door Door Salesman
description:

But what keeps people coming back to this job is that 1 time out of 10, when there's a need to be satiated, and only the sweet cherry-finish gleam of your new H-series model will do. When there's a pounding in their head, an aching for something better, and you drown in out with the robust hearty knock of your Seabreeze Type 5 Unit. Yes, those are the glory days when a sale is made, and you never know when opportunity will come a-knockin'. So we keep on a-walkin'.

title: House Full of Love
description: Roommates? No. No, he definitely never had any roommates. And they certainly never took up an entire rack on the fridge with their pizza boxes, with only one leftover slice inside, no. And they definitely didn't "accidentally" get stabbed to death in an "accidental" "accident." Wait, that sounds confusing. title: Terror on Fork Island
description: ​Their ship ran aground on the jagged reef of Bowtie Pasta Bay, a hellish oasis once thought to be a myth, meant to keep children in line. Any and all signs of solid food were forked away from their grasp as soon as they saw it. Weeks went by, subsisting only on liquids from the coconut milk streams and green tea springs, hiding in the shadows, waiting for a chance to make their escape. But there was no fooling the watchful eye of Forkon, the all-seeing, all-hungry Stab God.

description:

Anyway, this week we debate Mac vs. PC, the merits of Home Alone, determine which 5sf has packed the most dialogue in it and read out a bunch of silly names!

title: The Death of Cinco de Mayo
description:
And lo, did the tale of Jon and Brian, two massively unstable drinking partners unbound by time and unshaken by death, come to a bitter, sobbing, wretched end. Let this be a lesson to all: Some doors were never meant to be opened, some questions never meant to be asked. If you seek the true meaning of Cinco de Mayo, you seek to stare into the gaping, terrible chasm of eternity. And foolish travelers, believe me when I say the chasm will stare back. And it will tell you.

To shut.

The fuck.

Up.

title: Urine Trouble
description: Last week he put molasses on the windshield of his roommate's car, and diarrhea in the wiper fluid tank, but wound up just shitting all over his own face. That's what happens when you drink seven cups of coffee before riding the Tower of Terror. Anyway, his roommate drove around with a shit-filled wiper fluid tank for five months, and that is at least somewhat funny.

title: Crambox
description: Albert's crambox was home to many a blue feeling, sad thought and bummer memory. One could argue that a box can't hold words in speech form, and thus has no intrinsic value. But if you told that to Albert, he'd just get sad and go tell it to his crambox. It's a cycle of shame, repression and darkened closets for old Albert, and since that's all he's ever known, it's just the way he likes (and simultaneously hates) it.

title: Stoned Alone
description: ​Everyone's favorite mischievous prankster, Kevin McCallister, never left the booby-trapping game behind even as he grew into a shallow, lonely adulthood. As the cops would discover, upon getting a call from a neighbor about a weird smell from his house only to discover a rotting corpse covered in third-degree burns and house paint, it would be his undoing. They found vast amounts of THC in his body and ruled it an accidental death. But nobody bothered to notice the running water in the kitchen sink.

title: Test Notes
description:
Mrs. Blaumfgartner coughed loudly, and with a purpose. Her eyes were staring directly at the student in the back of the class. The scribbling of pencils dribbled to a stop. Soon, only the tick-tock of the second hand could be heard. Everyone knew Jimmy was in for it this time. "So, what sort of life-affirming statement have you got there this time, Jimmy?" She sniped. "Don't answer that. You'll be getting low marks for optimism, and I'll see you in after-school deflation." The rest of the class breathed in heavily and resumed their tests, making sure not to smile or nod their heads enthusiastically.

title: Life Choices
description: Hey Whatta Horse Yes This Is My Name For My Race Horse I'm Rich So Fuck You started out life as a powerful, preternaturally talented race horse, groomed for glory and winning the Triple Crown like it was a game of tic-tac-toe. Eventually, Hey Whatta realized he was meant for more, so he ran away from his billionaire oil magnate owners and enrolled in medical school. It was hard to adjust at first, but eventually he found his way - and a beautiful girl named Christy caught his eye in class. As they hung out more and more, she revealed to Hey Whatta her secret passion for the cello. Hearing her play brought him to tears - it revealed another world of creativity, of exploration and meaning to the gentle steed. Christy's parents eventually caught wind of their friendship and sent her away to another school, but she left behind sheet music of Hey Whatta's favorite piece she played, with a note telling him to never stop chasing what he was looking for, whether it be a medical degree, a chance to play at the London Philharmonic, or a finish line. title: Les Meowsérables
description: I've made peace with the team over Oscar Week, or Pawsc-Bark Wagk, or whatever they wanted to call it. Personally, I think there's virtue in making incredibly constricting, esoteric parodies of boring, award-baiting films that very few people have seen or care about. There's honor in it. There's the vague hope that an entertainment website will blog about our Oscar parodies, even though those will almost certainly not be as good as our other work, but hey, free press. It's worth it. And wheeling out some cute dogs in an attempt to "jazz up" the stale proceedings is just cheap pandering. That's my opinion and I'm sticking to it. Also, I shaved the cat.

title: PROBLEM CHILD
description: What's worse, Joe paid for his son's pilot lessons, helped pay off his loan to get the plane, and even stitched together the flight cap and jacket. All this should make you feel real bad for Joe, and hate his son. But that's because I didn't tell you Joe stabbed his son's mother to death right in front of his face. Now I bet you hate Joe and like his son. God you're such puppets.

description: ​Confidence is like a big-cocked shopping cart in a sea of tiny-dicked Audis. In fact, you should just say screw it to your brand new Audi and give it to us. We promise your wang will grow 60%.

title: Midget Break-In
description: ​Their big score was yet to come: Another house, just up the hill, foolishly stacked their gold bars on the bottom shelves of their armoire. For the Stout Bandits, it was a simple matter of sledding down the hill on a gold bar, loading them up into the Smart Car, and racing the sun to Mexico.

title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 1/28 - 2/1
description:
Feel great! Donate! http://5secondfilms.com/donate

While we wait for your money, we'll just lick our post-Super Bowl wounds by discussing science, the movie "Kinsey," poop and the relative predictability of 5sfs, Chad Ridderson makes a cameo appearance, and Maria shows us what soft screaming sounds like!

title: Chance Encounter
description: They even got him to autograph their divorce settlement with his kidney.

title: Foreplay
description: He walks around, finding girls from subway stations to park benches, handing out cards that advertise his ability to provide "Honey, Rose Petels (sic), Candles, and Bubble Baths." Rejection followed him at every turn, until one day he met a girl who couldn't take her eyes off him. A girl whose jaw remained permanently agape at the boldness of his offer.

title: Handicapable
description: Jan's Weirdling abilities extended further, allowing her to cook Rice-A-Roni 1.5x faster and to always have a classic Milton Berle joke on hand for any given situation. But they didn't extend much further than that.

title: A BP Oil Executive Gets Iced
description: Had British Petroleum bothered to research the "Bros Icing Bros" phenomenon, this horrible disaster could have been averted. Sadly, their ignorance was our loss, as we were forced to watch a high-ranking executive at the troubled company chug an excruciating amount of malt liquor, with absolutely no clear way to stop it.

title: Irresponsible Patriot
description: The combustibility of Premium brand beer is in sharp contrast to beers with low kerosene content, like your garden-variety pilsners or your mostly pedestrian lagers. In fact, a six-pack of Premium can get a commercial-size 18-wheeler over the hill on Highway 17 in Northern California. We discovered this fact during last year's 4OJ and frankly can't stop siphoning beer out of our gas tanks.

title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #223
description: Roid-rage fueled gun activists yearn for the days when "college ruled" and Hollywood agents and studios didn't just rely on a slew of unimaginative, violent, procedural cop shows.

title: Police Line
description: Warning: Boobsticks is still at large and considered extremely dangerous. If you have encountered Boobsticks, and you didn't have a machete handy, then you are dead and we're sorry Boobsticks killed you instead of old age.

title: Powered By Dreams
description: ​Back when California had those "rolling blackouts" to conserve power, Hollywood still glowed nice and bright, like a beacon of despair perched on a shining hill of shit. Mostly because there was a pretty huge casting call for That's So Raven.

title: More Behind The Scenes Action 1/21 - 1/25
description: Poo jokes. Just poo jokes. And even when the jokes aren't about poo, really, you can trace them back to poo somehow.

title: Chad "Tank" Ridderson's First Day at Work
description: Chad went on to overcome his deep sentimental attachment to those halcyon days of bodyshots, drunken stand-up paddleboard races and second-story ziplines, and he quickly rose up the ranks at SkremCorp. Promotion after promotion, Chad never lost sight of who he was, keeping that green notebook in his increasingly large, oaken desks wherever he went. As he grew older, it became a beacon of inspiration to himself and to many a Bro Hire that came through the SkremCorp doors. No one ever knew the contents of that seemingly magical notebook but Chad, and they were but a mere 11 words: "Have Dad Bribe My Superiors So I Don't Ever Get Fired.

title: 5sf's Comments of the Week 1/21 - 1/25
description:
5sf reads and answers your comments! Plus we launch a DONATE page because we are broke and can't buy any more props or beer! http://5secondfilms.com/donate

title: Studies Show
description: 9/10 is considered "The Golden Ratio" amongst the scientist-recommendation community. But every now and then, there is a tenth scientist who will not disagree - and they must be thinned from the herd. This process is called "Cresting," named after the infamous 10th dentist who couldn't bring himself to prefer Brand X over Crest Extra Whitening.

title: Power Lunch
description: Side effects to being this mega-shredded are as follows: Increased chance of heart failure, rage-cagin' city-wide rampages, and an inability to hold down any job other than lecturing high school assemblies on fitness by blowing up hot water bottles with just your lungpower.

title: Not OK!
description: A source close to Kelsey says, "He's a Leo, which contrasts with her sign. She wants a baby and he can't commit. He's jealous of her fame and they fight constantly. Any other fabricated, cotton candy, uninteresting, C-level soap opera, regurgitated bullshit you want me to spout about these two horrible people I've never met? How many pages do you have to fill before you get to Fashion Police?" Ms. Gunn's publicist could not be reached for comment, probably because we didn't even ask in the first place, since having no comment somehow makes for "juicier" drama.

title: Magnum π
description: Most of the time, he just shakes mathletes down for drug money. This is the most action he's gotten in weeks.

title: Nothing To Eat
description: Mischevio the Fridgegnome was out of ammo after that. He tried using the two-year-old hot sauce in the upper shelf of the fridge door, but nobody touched that stuff and neither, he tragically came to realize, would he.

title: The Big Move
description: Moving in a SmartCar makes you 140x better at Tetris. In some cases, you can even drive into the elevator and park right outside your new apartment door.

title: Rat Trap
description: In order to make the parts necessary for an oversized trap, the rats gathered together in the shape of a human, clambered into a suit, and traipsed down to the Silver Spring lumberyard. Unfortunately, their cover was blown, as any human knows you don't wear a suit to a lumberyard, and the rats dispersed immediately. They just wound up buying a pre-made trap off of eBay.

title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #222
description: While riding the rails through Mexico a hungry officer worker was sucked into a comfy couch with his poker player lesbian friends.

title: Slayer
description: Can you change a lesbian? Should you change a lesbian? Isn't it completely none of your business whether you can or can't change a person who loves the person she wants to love? The answers are yes, yes, and no, but only if you can beat her four-of-a-kind.

title: Comfy Couch
description: You didn't "lose" your car keys in there for four hours. They were borrowed by your alternate universe friends to help move some a new bed into an apartment a few blocks down the couch. Also, speaking of which, remember how there used to be a rollout bed attached to the couch? Well...you weren't using it.

title: Another Day at the Office
description: Fellow employees describe him as "cheerful," "easy to get along with," "attentive and focused," "comes in late on Mondays," and "eats shit." Needless to say, he passed the annual review with flying colors.

title: Montezuma's Revenge
description: Kelsey's not wrong - after all, ​"Montezuma" is Nahuatl for "Master Cleanse." Not many people know that, primarily because I made it up. So really, only I knew it. But since it's not a fact, I didn't exactly "know" it either. And since I knew something that isn't real, that means I'm not real, either. So, goodbye then. It's been fun.

title: Ol' Rail Riding Rodney
description: On account 'a being a skeleton since the days of President James Madison, Ol' Rodney's seen some things you people wouldn't darn near believe. Merchant ships on fire off the shoulder of Fort Sumter. He's watched I-beams clatter in the dark abandoned factories near the Hooverville Gates. And because his eternal soul won't shut up about none of it, all them there moments will be preserved in time, like bones in the dirt!

title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 1/14 - 1/18
description: Howdy-doody. This week, we engage in a series of truly terrible puns, get some dog exercises in, confess what our middle names are, try in vain to defend our inclusion of black people in 5sfs, and travel at the speed of light.

title: What Mel Said
description:
As you can see, it takes us a little while to savage pop culture news so excellently, because getting the perfect joke is just worth it.

You know, the sad truth is, Mel Gibson is a good enough filmmaker to have made a better 5sf about this whole thing.

title: Dude Magnet
description: She read "The Game." She knows what's up. Now it's time to select a mark from the group, demonstrate her value, establish kino, and ditch the baby in a swing somewhere while they go make out behind a Red Robin.

title: Beach Party
description: I know what some of you might say. "How could any party be lame with Kelsey and Olivia there?" Well, they were talking about Spanx for the better part of three hours, and insisted on an all-Van Morrison party soundtrack. So there's your answer, internet.

title: Hungover Barber Shop Quartet
description: Their gig at Rudy's Senior Discount Summer Nights Bash got really out of hand. D'Artagnan did a keg stand off of the barbasol tank, Jensen mainlined a thick stream of heroin for two minutes straight, Aloysious saw into another dimension and Franklin became a bullgod.

description: Always make sure to ask your Fortune Teller for precise clarification as to who, or what exactly, your wife may be seeing. If it's a turnip, or a Bachman Turner Overdrive reunion, or another man, or a shellfish & bluegrass festival, or perhaps someone in the room besides you, you won't know until you ask.

description: The winnings totaled somewhere around $300,000,000. It wasn't enough to beat his boss' legal team when they successfully argued that placing the ticket on her desk amounted to "gifting" her with it. The only silver lining to his dark cloud: Her legal team cost $299,999,991.23, which meant she still had to fish through her purse for change when she bought a slice of victory pie that night.

title: Study Party
description: He had a killer final the next day. Using his knowledge of physics, he absolutely nailed the beer pong section, but Professor Brodacious wound up giving him an F when fellow students accused him of being a nerd and using physics.

title: The Ultimate Wingman
description: ​He's since improved from his old wingmanning days, but get a few drinks in him and he'll still wind up telling people all about what a tender lover you are - except now he tells it to the dudes he's just punched in the face, which is a step up I guess.

title: The Nutritionist
description: Faster than a cayenne pepper-inspired bowel movement. More powerful than a fish diet rich in anti-oxidants! Able to leap tall stacks of health magazines with theories and research that cancel each other out...in a single bound!

description: Frustrated at the lack of job opportunities for skilled lovers who've been around the block a few times and know a few things about life that some fancy schmancy degree can't teach you, Barry contacted a local video productions company to track him over the course of a wild, hellish couple of decades, in the efforts to document his whole life's work and perhaps one day pitch himself as a roadie for Eddie Money's tour -- truly, the greatest job Barry could think of at the time.

title: Last Words
description: His will left his AHHHHHHH to his GGGBBBBB(radio static). The family lawyer could do nothing about it.

title: The Ol' "Snakes In A Peanut Can" Trick
description: Marks Toys sold these "Snake'm Prank'm Cans" for one glorious summer in 1984, and ever since they discontinued production, it's become something of a collector's item. Mainly in Thailand, for whatever reason.

title: A Fat Kid Mulls His Options
description: After this, it's time to pick a pair of cargo shorts, Tivas, and trim the facial hair until only the neckbeard remains unshaven. And then it's time to troll the internet.

title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #220
description: Mr Silly woke up to the feeling of a hand up his ass from a person who's name he couldn't remember and whether or not he was paid up.

description: This is the second time his money laundering front has gone under before it even started. First time, it was a "Fluff-n-food" "restaurandromat" that failed to attract customers who wanted a great chicken parm while their whites were in the dryer. The organized crime families didn't even need to blow that one up. They just sat in lawn chairs across the street, watching Joey slowly go out of business through binoculars.

title: Mr. Silly's Song Time
description: Mr. Silly is a puppet of few words, though his song collection is vast, eclectic, and betrays the sensitive soul within. Thousands upon thousands of B-sides, live recordings and mono versions swirl in his head. To the untrained ear, the world of music Mr. Silly dove into is ostensibly a cacophony of noise. But each lyric, each melody harkens back to a throbbing, still-living memory of his past, and those memories collide, overlap and connect to bring clarity and focus to the shape of his life, just as each part of a symphony comes together in a roiling crescendo of beauty. Also, he fucking hates Ben.

He would warp through time with the greatest of ease and the saddest of consequences, and one day he was found face down in a puddle of vomit - finally, a man unstuck from time, albeit stuck to something else entirely.

description: Santa enters a house on the most magical of days only to forget that he was given the slip by a mean friend; if only he had the post-interaction smile reduction quantifier.

title: Post-Interaction Smile Reduction Quantifier
description: The highly scientific PISRQ (often referred to as "Piss Rock" for short) can analyze the fall of the mouth corners as a person turns away from a friend or acquaintance, and determine whether that person is full of sunshine and warmth or bitterness and a desire to choke things until the police arrive. Piss Rock is accurate to within a percentage point.

He doesn't even do anything down there. Just marvels at his ability to make it this far through the powerful security, sends out a tweet from as close to the vagina as possible, and then dons a new identity, a new set of clothes, a new rental car, a new set of credit cards, and a new town to bizarrely terrorize.

title: Forgettingtown
description: It all started on a night where it might have been raining and dark and such, when a sexy, smoldering woman (maybe a smoldering man? Will research later) walked in the door. I think I worked there. She was asking about a door. Wait, no, she walked in the door. I was the one asking about the door, because I don't know what a door is. One thing I did know was, I had to take the case. This door conspiracy wasn't going to solve itself.

title: How Santa Gets Into Every House On Christmas
description: With every limb snapping, stretching and groaning to hundreds of feet long, flesh elongating and twisting around rooftop antennas, and organs compressing and rearranging to fit through steel-barred windows, Santa truly is a wonder to behold for girls and boys of all ages. Lo, young Johnny! Hear his jolly screech as his neck extends to burst through the floorboards! And sweet Alice, gaze yonder as Kris Kringle's eyeballs collapse and give way to a pair of tentacles, wrapping around the family dog! Merry Christmas to all!

title: The Most Magical of Days
description: Rum in the egg nog. Peppermint schnapps in the cocoa. Mulled wine. Cider. However you shut the fuck up this holiday season, do it with friends and family by your side and Christmas in your heart. Happy holidays from all of us at 5secondfilms!

title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #217
description: While making gingerbread gift cards for his stoner atheist friends, Santa discovers Misses Claus loves trains and ruining marriages.

title: What Do You Want For Christmas?
description: You'd be surprised by how often Santa gets asked to help terminate a failed marriage. Let's just say he goes through a box of pantyhose and a stick of Ruby Red Passionfruit Extra Gloss nearly every week.

title: Polar Express
description: Just like Robert Zemeckis' delightful family film, you can watch this "Polar Express" in 3D as well. All of the marital strife, quiet desperation and sad frustration feels like it's coming right out of the screen at you! But no elf genitalia. The elf genitalia does not come out of the screen at you.

title: Merry Christmas from 5SF
description: It's almost Christmas! We decided to make an e-card with some of our best holiday 5sfs over the years. Hope you enjoy it. Check out the cheesy e-card we made it for, and if you enjoy it, spread the word!

title: St. Lawrence College Promos
description: Hey! St. Lawrence College hit us up to make them some hilarious promos. We had fun. Hope you enjoy them!

title: Atheist Uncle
description: For years, his daily checklist consisted of screencapping religious facebook posts that he's trolled, and posting them online. It wasn't until he laid on his deathbed decades later, staring down oblivion, that he converted to Not Being A Douchebag About It. They even brought in an agnostic minister to make it official.

title: Santa Snacks
description: In a fit of marijuana-induced mania, Santa also mocked up the newspapers announcing his spectacular failure at distributing presents, and instead put the papers in every coffee shop and on every doorstep the same morning. It was his way of saying sorry, but people just wondered why it was called "News Times.

title: Santa Gives Up
description: Santa knows you like that one thing at the other place, whatever it was. Go nuts. Just don't spend it all in one place, ho ho ho! The joke of course being that you can only spend it in...you know what, never mind, Santa's just gonna go now.

title: XXXmas Cookies
description: Should XXXmas Cookies spring to life, then impishly run away daring you to catch them, fear not: Their big floppy gingerbread tits and dicks will slow them down considerably, enabling you to close the distance on them around corners.

description:
Christmas Week begins at 5sf! We debate what Butt Stuff is, tell a classic joke and Adrian, the creator of the most popular 5sf ever, stops by!

Also, support our kid actors, The Sloans! They're in a new sketch from Stan Lee's World of Heroes that's actually pretty funny (and shot at our place)! http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L4Yk3DDM6YE

description: Plug in your lawn decorations, heat up your apple cider, and call your lawyer. Because Christmas is coming, and you're wanted for killing a hooker.

description: The strength of family togetherness can endure most anything, including but not limited to: Hair gels that add great sheen but provide no body, restaurants that lie about their so-called "bottomless" mimosa brunch specials for Ma's Day, and those especially dark times when you don't Smell Good. It all started when one accused the other of nipping a still-cooling apple crumble from the windowsill, and the other party retaliated by tying her lovely daughter to train tracks and letting an oncoming locomotive blast her screaming, crying body to pieces.

title: Pizza
description: Domino's has this special 2-for-1 deal where you eat the second pizza your girlfriend was supposed to have, because you just got broken up with. It's called "Ordering Two Pizzas Alone at Domino's.

title: The 1st Annual Empty Chair Spelling Bee
description: If your child has a really, really hard time spelling "supple," count your blessings. Or your child may just be stupid, in which case you probably don't have many blessings to count anyway.

title: Cockpit
description: The black box they recovered from the wreckage was immediately seized by the government, and caused such a fit of inappropriate laughter in the break room at FBI headquarters that Simmons lost focus and got his hand caught in the blender. Surveillance footage of the "blender incident" went viral and caused one man to drive his car off a bridge from trying to watch it on his smartphone. title: Mr. Trump Goes to Washington
description:
After he fucked a frog onstage while screaming "FAKE NEWS" in Russian, a fountain of piss exploded and soaked the Mormon Tabernacle Choir, who were singing from blank musical pages in recently-purchased manila folders. The Rockettes were forced to clap as an effigy of Meryl Streep was set on fire.

The entire gathered news media published nothing but ellipses and the words "I don't understand" over and over again. Meanwhile, under cover of night, ninja turtle Mitch McConnell repealed Obamacare and replaced it with a pre-existing condition - racism.

There, that covers it. Fuck you and fuck this shitty country.

title: Goodbye 2016
description:
NOG® will not be stopped by your pitiful newscasts. NOG® will not be rebranded to save face, even as it swallows your soul. NOG® has been here sine the Elder Times, and it shall remain long after your kind has been swept away, even after this year which you so quaintly refer to as "the worst ever."

This Christmas, the rivers will run beige with NOG®

title: Christmas Pageant
description:
Parents: It is so hard being a parent, am I right on this one? Back me up, adults. The kids have Christmas pageants that you have to attend, and when they come home they projectile-vomit the contents of their rotting sack lunches onto your windows! What is a Grown Joan (or if you are a daddy, a Complete Pete) to do?

There's GON®, the new product from the Makers that will cleanse your heart with the interlocking flavor fibers of shiny goodness! GON® can jazz up almost any slate, release a hot load of sparkle on any surface! Make your windows taste and feel better than ever before with our patented Wipe-It Technology©, and see how the new day will come for your face through your very own home!

GON®. Questions On.

title: The Plot Twist Killer
description:
He stalked in the night, waiting for the time to strike. With every blink, he whisked away to another location, another angle, hidden in plain sight. He laid with the rat in the wall, peering back to see the scratchings of its words. He watched the arms of Mr. Shadows stretch into the bathroom, watched the faint burst of light in the distance wash away the creature's features like an acid bath. He witnessed the stitches and staples threading the flesh of Jerry Klobb, heard Ellen's piercing laughter as she punctured his body. When he was finished, he would delete them from existence with a pitch-black shroud and the words THE END. If he chose to restart their cycle of want and torture, he did so with a press of a button. Their lives hung, and hung, and hung again in the balance of his murderous fingers.

Then, when he was through with destroying and rebooting realities, he closed his browser window and resumed working. He never thought much about these lives after he was done with them. He might show the extent of his cruelty to a friend, and see whether they laughed or not. Perhaps sometimes, he'd leave a comment - a humorous pun, a meme, the phrase "I Am the Plot Twist Killer" - but he never, ever, ever cared.

And why would he? He's you.

title: My Roommate Mr. Shadows
description:
Andrew had a lot of adjusting to do after moving into the house. He never met the guy whose room he would be inheriting, but he sure collected a lot of men's beauty magazines. The other guy was always hogging the bathroom and never had much to say. And then there was Mr. Shadows.

The rules of the house, which were posted inside Mr. Shadows' water heater closet where he slept, detailed exactly what humans were and weren't. When they were alive, they were not food. When they were dead and rotting, they were food. If the cops arrived before you could eat the body, they weren't food anymore. And human food was for humans.

Mr. Shadows would abuse this last rule time and again, like when he crawled into the refrigerator once the lightbulb broke, or when he ordered raw sausage casings on Amazon as "snacks for everyone." The cake was the last straw, something Andrew's girlfriend left for him in anticipation of his birthday tomorrow. Mr. Shadows saw the cake sort of looked like him, and decided to have it all to himself. He even lit the candle, assuming that's just what one does before eating cake. Of course, lighting it from a distance took some work, and the closer he brought his face to the flame, the more his nose disappeared. He tried to be careful about that, but this time he was just too excited.

Now it was all over the floor, ruined. Andrew threw it away and scolded Shadows for going through his cupboard. Then he retired to the living room, where he slept on the couch while Jerry was still in the process of moving out.

The sound of wet gristle slapping on the floor woke Andrew up later in the evening. He sat upright on the couch, rubbing his eyes. Then he saw Mr. Shadows, staring out the window.

A house was on fire some number of streets down, illuminating everything in its faraway flicker. It was just bright enough that it managed to shine faintly on Mr. Shadows' face, carving the front of his head away from sight. Only the hollow interior of the back of his head was visible, like a broken mannequin inside an empty store. Then it spoke.

"So many rules," he said to Andrew. "So many little rules." He turned to look at the couch and the half of his face furthest from the window returned to view, revealing half of a wide set of incisors bent in a crooked smile.

They both heard a muddy thud from the bathroom. Like a body falling. Andrew looked in its direction, praying that Shadows would look too. But he just stared at Andrew with his one visible eye.

"Sleep well," he said, before turning the lights on and skittering to the bathroom. Andrew fell asleep to the churning sounds of chewing and slurping, organs vanishing into an unseen dimension, blood wiping itself off the tile with the sound of deep, sensuous licking.

It was the last peaceful night's sleep Andrew would get.

title: To Make The Perfect Man
description:
Ellen had long since been banned from practicing surgery, but they couldn't stop her in time from barricading the men's bathroom door and filling the room with her clothes and soup cans. Police weren't able to make it to the hospital just yet, so until then the staff would have to make sure no one came in or out. It's not like Ellen was capable of much in there anyway.

Until Jerry stopped by to use the bathroom.

Ellen had been screening each potential suitor through a self-made peephole in the door, and finally she found someone knocking on the door who suited her tastes. He just needed a few adjustments.

******

By the time police finally burst open the door and took Ellen away, Jerry was gone. He stumbled out of the room in a daze, shuffling past his car in the parking lot and onto the long stretch of lonesome road towards home. As his skin loosened around the puncture holes, every step jangled the staples in his face more and more, scraping against the open nerves under his flesh. He couldn't feel it, nor could he care. He was beautiful.

The blood had congealed over his left eye, shutting it completely. But his right eye could still see through the pinhole of the mask to the outside world, to the mirror in front of him. And what he saw was breathtaking. A bold push-broom mustache, the likes of which he could never grow himself. A strong nose, proud brow. Everything was smooth and pliable. He had achieved his dreams.

It was a shame, he realized, that the rest of him didn't match up. Everywhere else he looked, he saw the flabby, rough, pale skin of his former self. It sickened him that his old body couldn't live up to the promise of his new face.

He dug in deep to the skin in the crook of his arm, and pulled. Like wet tissue paper, it sloughed off with a bare squick. He saw the tendons underneath, the beautiful bone. He grabbed more, pulling up his forearm until the flesh inverted around the bones of his fingers like a glove.

He grasped at the skin above his pectorals, his scapulas, his trapezius, peeling them off in globs and strips. The pile of blood and gristle grew at his feet as he shredded more and more of himself in a drug-fueled stupor. All the while, he never took his eye off of his new, beautiful face.

He reached for his kneecaps, but the blood loss caused him to lose his balance and he fell over, breaking his arms in the process. His exposed muscles twitched and flexed like a symphony in red, writhing like a fish out of water, covering the bathroom tile in his slop.

He was finally perfect, he thought, before the spark went out in his brain forever.

title: Necessary Evil
description:
The doctors told him he needed to spend less time sitting down on the toilet, but it was his quiet place. The only place he could hide safely from the outside world and breathe for a minute. Nevertheless,  they gave him some suppositories and instructions. He waited at the bathroom door in the hospital, pounding on it a few times, but to no avail: Some woman was laughing in there. Embarrassment overtook him and he held it all the way until he got back home, stuck in traffic because of some raging house fire a few streets down.

When he got inside, he felt around for the light switch, but couldn't grasp it. The only light turned on was in the bathroom, and it illuminated the hallway faintly enough that he could paw his way along the wall to get to it.

He sat down, blissfully ignorant of the doctor's instructions, and took out his phone. A few minutes passed by in silence as he whisked through all his usual news sites, made a funny tweet, and played a few rounds of Noodles.

Then he noticed his pills were gone.

Frantically, he swiped at every errant towel and cleaning product in the room to see where they could have gone. No shelf or cabinet held them. They just disappeared. He groaned at the thought of having to go back to the pharmacy so soon. Embarrassment seemed to follow him around like a cloud.

A groan came from the pipes, like a metal belly inhaling and exhaling. A chip of paint cracked loose from the wall as the sound travelled closer, closer, snaking around the corners and rumbling upwards. Then it stopped.

Frozen in his seat, the next sound he heard was the clack and clink of long, old fingernails in a ceramic bowl, scraping themselves closer. The next thing he felt was a wet, gnarled finger brush against the skin of his inner thigh.

As always, it was trying to help.

title: Rats In The Wall
description:
That night, Jane and Kevin made love, if something so methodical and brief could be considered love. It was one more try to have a baby, in a year of dozens of such attempts. But something was different about it all, when her fiancé finally spent himself. His breath sounded ragged and wet, like something was stuck in the back of his throat. His exhales sounded like inhales, and vice versa. He got up to use the bathroom, and right as the faucet turned on, she swore she could hear that sound again from where she sat on the bed.

That summer night was so hot, even with every window open and the ceiling fan lazily rocking above, she couldn't bear to lie in the sheets. She slid her feet against Kevin's, whose toes always managed to be cold. Tonight, it was just what she needed, and it helped her drift off to sleep. 

A week later, she got the happiest news she could have received: They were going to be parents. Before, they were thinking about moving to a cheaper neighborhood; now, all they could do was pick out colors for the nursery in Kevin's old office. This finally catapulted them into the same phase of their lives as all their friends, who were already raising 2- or 3-year-olds, and the baby showers and get-togethers seemed to crackle with a newfound common ground. Finally, their life was getting back on track.

The delivery wasn't supposed to happen for another 2 weeks, but Jane's baby was simply impatient to join the world, it seemed. She writhed and thrashed in pain, just like the classes and videos said she would. But to Kevin, her eyes seemed bloodshot, her neck straining with veins he didn't know she had. It didn't seem right, and the doctors told him to go outside. They needed to do a C-section, and the baby wasn't in the right position for it. This would be better handled with him out of the room.

Sitting outside was driving him mad. He remembered her book, the one she was reading about becoming a new mother - in their earlier panic to get to the hospital, she left it at home. He could make himself useful and get back in time for the delivery, and she'd have something to read during her stay afterwards. He didn't waste another second, running two red lights just to get home.

A police siren turned on right behind Kevin, freezing him in his seat until the cop car weaved around him to barrel on ahead. By this time, they reached a residential area - what was the cop going for, if not him? And what was that bright light around the corner, on their street?

Kevin turned left and saw a raging fire coming from their house, flames towering higher and higher. It swallowed the tree he planned to use for his daughter's treehouse, it took the backyard she and her new puppy would play in. It caved in the roof above the nursery and heated up the front windows until they shattered.

Hours later, when the hoses had drowned the last of the flames away and the fire trucks turned to leave, Kevin walked to the center of what was once their home, standing on the still-smoldering ashes. His phone buzzed incessantly in the passenger seat of his car. It was the 10th call in a row he missed, all from the hospital. He couldn't hear it.

He crouched down closer to a mound of charcoal and ash, clearing some of the debris away. There was a half-melted candle, with pink stripes. Like something for a birthday cake. He remembered those old party candles now, last time he saw them they were shoved in the back of one of those kitchen drawers. They'd gone missing for months.

Something in the ash took a breath.

---

title: The Legend of the Hooky Killer
description:
They set up a perimeter around the woods. Ever since the Harbinger and his brother went on those rampages years back, no one was taking any chances. Every available officer on the force had every conceivable exit surrounded. Each sweep of flashlight beams, each crunch of twigs underneath their boots, brought them no closer to their mark. He may as well have been gone.

Sergeant Patterson's latest sting was a bust. But he was sure he was here. He sent his best men out to secure the rim. Syben. Barter. Goodwin. Ramos. All trustworthy men, and damn good at their jobs. No sign of the man with the gleaming hook.

They wanted to pack it in. But Patterson knew something wasn't right. This killer was different than the others this town had seen. Even those fitness freaks who tried converting people to their cult a year ago. That was forced assimilation, but they crept around silently. This guy...this guy wanted attention. He wanted a show. And here was his stage. It didn't make sense.

Sarge made the call: They were staying the night, taking it in shifts. As they hunkered down for the long stakeout, Patterson put Ramos up as first watch. 

"This guy's late to his own funeral," the Sergeant muttered to no one, as if to steel his resolve for his long, final night ahead.

title: The Ritual
description:
One by one, people were ripped from their homes in the city. Fingernail scratches dotted the tops of doorways, second-story windows were shattered, evidence of women, children and men clutching in vain for dear life. Curiously, despite the shower of glass, wood and blood in each foyer, every bed was made perfectly.

Everyone was brought to a clearing, hovering up above the treeline, suspended in mid-air. Struggling only caused them to spin slowly in place, as if they were impaled by some invisible bar through the abdomen. After the screaming subsided, the chosen ones'  thoughts turned to each other. Inexplicably, the fear they felt as a group started to give way to...jealousy.

Something snaked in and around their brains, curdling their thoughts into hate. It started with the personal trainer, who noticed a dozen pairs of hollow eyes leering at her with rage. They wanted her body. They wanted it to be taken from her and given to them.

No one could move to attack her, but as if sensing their thoughts, an invisible force began to drain the life away from her. A straw sucking from the inside, vacuum-sealing her flesh to her ribs, eyes rolling back into her skull, hair dissolving into clumps. She broke in half at the waist before she was even finished, and her bony feet touched the back of her shriveled head as she hung there, lifeless, spinning in the void above the clearing with the rest of the mob.

Smiles stretched across their faces. They could feel it. They could feel the burning inside, the fruits of their mental, hateful labor blossoming within. It felt so good to watch the subcutaneous fat shudder away, shrinking and sucking and withering, revealing taut muscles and slim waists. A peal of laughter caught fire with the group, as their bodies took the shape of dreams - as if the person they wished they were when they looked in the mirror had stepped out of the glass to replace them, mind body and soul.

Slowly they were lowered back to Earth, bare feet feeling the blades of grass. Their legs flexed as they wriggled their toes in the dirt, each one a perfect, and perfectly absent, specimen. They looked up. The trainer, or what was left of her, was still hovering in the sky, a husk dripping the ash of dead flesh like snowflakes. It fell softly around them, but didn't stain their clothes or skin. It slid right off. Nothing could penetrate them now. The master would see to that. Now all they had to do was march.

The cleansing began.

title: Family Recipe
description:
The child-proof locks on the cabinets were not enough for Jean. She knew the baby could smell the chemicals under the sink, clear across the house from the crib in his room. So they weatherstripped every door and bought an air purifier for the nursery, but that still didn't suffice. Jean heard noises at night, discordant creaks underneath the house as if rats were biting on piano wire. She became obsessed with caulking every crack in the walls, stitching the small gaps in the floorboards tighter and tighter with poorly-drilled screws at awkward, splintering angles. Like the floor, she was winding herself tighter and tighter, a rag doll about to burst at the seams.

Her husband became concerned enough to finally phone her doctor, and as he repeated her behavior into the receiver, he slowly understood what was happening before Dr. Richards could even diagnose it.

"I would say, Steven, based on what you've just told me, that Jean appears to be suffering from..."

"Shhh."

Steven didn't care about the diagnosis. He needed silence.

"Do you hear that, Doctor?"

"No, I'm afraid I don't follow..."

Steven heard it again. The sound of someone else on the line, trying in vain to hold their breath.

"I'll call you back." He hung up and slowly exited the office. "Jean?" He said, rounding the corner into the main hallway. "What did you hear, honey?"

He looked cautiously into the nursery as he continued down the hall, each footstep eliciting another creak from the tense, splitting boards. The mobile was spinning softly above the crib, a dolphin, a whale, an octopus with all eight legs snipped off. Choking hazards, she said. The baby wasn't inside.

Steven turned. His pant leg caught on one of the jutting screws, and he tripped to land on his face, the bridge of his nose breaking on contact with a bent nail.

As he passed out, he saw the shadow of Jean's legs spill across the light leading into the kitchen. He was just in time for dinner.

title: Home Is Hell
description:
For Joe, coming home to West Virginia was like being denied his existence. The VA lost his paperwork. The shrink would routinely forget his name, prescribe him bottles of sedatives with names he couldn't pronounce. People he went to high school with didn't look at him as he'd cross the street to the grocery store - and when the produce section's automatic misters turned on, they'd play a cute little "thunder clap" sound which sent Joe diving for cover. That, he noticed, got them looking. Looking right at him. He felt strangely grateful for these moments, as they confirmed he wasn't just a ghost haunting a better life he left behind.

Eventually, the court ordered that Joe was a danger to his daughter, and could only see her with an appointed psychiatrist in tow, a stern woman named Alice who clearly hated children. Why was he the danger, and not her? Joe loved his daughter, from the moment he held her, to every time he caught her before she could fall off a bike or a swing set. He was her guardian angel, she made him feel whole, like a protector. She made him forget about the door he sent his men through in Kandahar.

He woke up in bed at the memory of the door, but it dawned on him that he wasn't sleeping either. It took him days to sleep, even after weaning himself off of coffee. Was the entire day a dream, and this the reality?

His closet door creaked open. It had holes punched in it from when Joe went to a dark place, but now they looked like bullet holes. The moon was so bright, the brown wood looked like it was painted blue. Just like that door in Kandahar.

Joe got up, walked through the door, and never came back.
